Title: Prediction Intervals for Exponential Smoothing State Space Models.
Author-Name: Hyndman, R.J. 
Author-X-Name-First: R.J.
Author-X-Name-Last: Hyndman
Author-Email: Rob.Hyndman@BusEco.monash.edu.au
Author-Name: Koehler, A.B.
Author-X-Name-First: A.B.
Author-X-Name-Last: Koehler
Author-Name: Ord, J.K.
Author-X-Name-First: J.K.
Author-X-Name-Last: Ord
Author-Name: Snyder, R.D.
Author-X-Name-First: R.D.
Author-X-Name-Last: Snyder
Keywords: Forecast distribution; Holt-Winters method; Structural models
Length: 22 pages
Abstract: The main objective of this paper is to provide analytical expression for forecast 
    variances that can be used in prediction intervals for the exponential smoothing 
    methods. These expressions are based on state space models with a single source of 
    error that underlie the exponential smoothing methods. In cases where an ARIMA model 
    also underlies an exponential smoothing method, there is an equivalent state space 
    model with the same variance expression. We also discuss relationships between these 
    new ideas and previous suggestions for finding forecast variances and prediction 
    intervals for the exponential smoothing methods. 
