Title: The Missing Link: Using the NBER Recession Indicator to Construct Coincident 
    and Leading Indices of Economic Activity.
Author-Name: Issler, J.V.
Author-X-Name-Last: Issler
Author-X-Name-First: J.V.
Author-Name: Vahid, F.
Author-X-Name-Last: Vahid
Author-X-Name-First: F.
Author-Email: Farshid.Vahid@BusEco.monash.edu.au
Keywords: Coincident and Leading Indicators; Business Cycle; Canonical Correlation; 
    Instrumental Variable Probit; Encompassing
Length: 34 pages
Abstract: We use the information content in the decisions of the NBER Business cycle 
    Dating Committee to construct coincident and leading indices of economic 
    activity for United States. Specifically, we use canonical correlation analysis 
    to filter out the noisy information contained in the coincident series. 
    Finally, to construct our preferred coincident index of the U.S. business cycle, 
    we take account of measurement error in the commonly used coincident series by 
    using instrumental-variable methods. The resulting index is a simple linear 
    combination of four coincident series that encompassed
    currently popular coincident indices. 
