Length: 20 pages
Abstract: Despite the commonly held belief that aggregate data display short-run 
    comovement, there has been little discussion about the econometric consequences 
    of this feature of the data. We use exhaustive Monte-Carlo simulations to 
    investigate the importance of restrictions implied by common-cyclical features 
    for estimates and forecasts based on vector autoregressive models.
